Chinese tech company Huawei reported a 75.9-percent rise in net profit in 2021, although revenue dropped to 636.8 billion following U.S. sanctions, Chief Financial Officer Meng Wanzhou told a press conference in Shenzhen on March 28. Despite the decline in revenue, Meng said Huawei's ability to "make a profit and generate cash flows is increasing," adding that the company will continue to invest in talent and research.